  "text": "Both acupuncture and moxibustion are considered to be the external therapy [CITATION_1] , and based on the mechanism of acupuncture analgesia, we presumed that the moxibustion analgesia in CVH rats might be due to the induction of dynorphin and orphanin-FQ system in the spinal cord. We performed the pilot experiment and found that WM could increase the level of spinal dynorphin in CVH rats [CITATION_2] , which holds our interests to further study the spinal dynorphin and orphanin-FQ system in moxibustion analgesia.",
